7":"1217","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1257":"1257","1202":"1202","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","before 1170":"before 1170","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Of Wiloughby, Lincolnshire England":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, , England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Willoughby","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Willoughby, for example in Leicestershire, Lincolnshire, Nottinghamshire, and Warwickshire. They are named from an Old English +<i>wilig</i> ‘willow’ + Old Norse <i>bȳ</i> ‘farmstead, village’."],"variants":[{"name":"Wilby","meanings":["habitational name from any of the places called Wilby, in Suffolk, Norfolk, and Northamptonshire. The first placename is probably named from an Old English <i>wilig</i> ‘willow’ + Old English <i>bēag</i> ‘circle, ring’; the Norfolk placename derives from Old English <i>wilig</i> + <i>bēag</i> or Old Norse <i>bý</i> ‘farmstead, village’; the Northamptonshire placename derives from the Old Norse personal name <i>Vili</i> + <i>bý</i>.","Redmonds has demonstrated that in the parish of Hipperholme, and subsequently elsewhere in Yorkshire, <i>Wilby</i> occurs as a variant of   Willoughby  .","English:"]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":45,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":54,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William de Willoughby x was born in 1170, in Lincolnshire, England, his father, Hugh de Willoughby, was 35 and his mother, Frethesende Cockerington, was 21. He married Maud Fulletby in 1189, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1225, in Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1170–1225":"1170–1225","1202–Male":"1202–Surnud","–1220":"–1220","1210–1257":"1210–1257","1217–1257":"1217–1257","1135–1205":"1135–1205","1150–1260":"1150–1260","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","Abt 1217":"umbes 1217","1217":"1217","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1257":"1257","1202":"1202","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","before 1170":"enne 1170","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Of Wiloughby, Lincolnshire England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, , England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1170–1225":"1170–1225","1202–Male":"1202–Kuollut","–1220":"–1220","1210–1257":"1210–1257","1217–1257":"1217–1257","1135–1205":"1135–1205","1150–1260":"1150–1260","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","Abt 1217":"noin 1217","1217":"1217","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1257":"1257","1202":"1202","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","before 1170":"ennen vuotta 1170","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Of Wiloughby, Lincolnshire England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, , England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1170–1225":"1170–1225","1202–Male":"1202–Décédé","–1220":"–1220","1210–1257":"1210–1257","1217–1257":"1217–1257","1135–1205":"1135–1205","1150–1260":"1150–1260","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","Abt 1217":"environ 1217","1217":"1217","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1257":"1257","1202":"1202","1135":"1135","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","before 117